description:
The screenshot displays a maximized Corel WordPerfect 7 window. The main editing area is largely empty, with a vertical blue dotted line indicating the right margin.  The status bar at the bottom of the window shows the following:

* **"Insert"**: This indicates the program is currently in Insert mode, where typing will add characters without overwriting existing ones. 
* **"HP LaserJet 4/4M Plus PS"**: This shows the currently selected printer.
* **"Select"**: This indicates that the current mouse mode is for selecting text or objects. 
* **"Pg 1"**: This displays the current page number.
* **"Ln 1"**: This displays the current line number the cursor is on.
* **"Pos 1"**: This displays the current character position the cursor is on within the current line.

The screenshot shows a maximized Corel WordPerfect 7 window with a blank document open. The right margin is marked by a vertical blue dotted line.  At the bottom of the window, the status bar displays the following from left to right: "Insert," "HP LaserJet 4/4M Plus PS," "Select," "Pg 1," "Ln 1," and "Pos 1."

The screenshot shows a maximized Corel WordPerfect 7 window with a largely empty editing area.  A vertical blue dotted line marks the right margin. The status bar at the bottom of the window displays "Insert," "HP LaserJet 4/4M Plus PS," "Select," "Pg 1," "Ln 1," and "Pos 1," indicating the program mode, selected printer, mouse mode, page number, line number, and character position, respectively.

The screenshot shows a maximized Corel WordPerfect 7 window with a "Save As" dialog box open. The dialog box is titled "Corel Office -- Save As" and has a menu bar with the options "File," "Edit," "View," "Tools," "Favorites," and "Help."  The main area of the dialog box is empty. 

New UI Elements:
- A dialog box titled "Corel Office -- Save As".

The screenshot shows the Corel WordPerfect 7 window with a "Save As" dialog box open. The dialog box is titled "Corel Office - Save As" and has several fields and buttons.

New UI Elements:
- A dialog box titled "Corel Office - Save As" is now visible. It features:
    - A "Save in:" field with a dropdown menu.
    - A "File name:" field.
    - An "As type:" field with a dropdown menu displaying "WordPerfect 6.0/6.1 (*.wpd;*.wpt)"
    - A "Password protect" checkbox.
    - "Save", "Close" buttons. 
- The "Save As" dialog box partially obscures the main editing area of the Corel WordPerfect 7 window.

The screenshot shows the Corel WordPerfect 7 window with the "Save As" dialog box open. The dialog box is titled "Corel Office - Save As - MyFiles".  The "Save as type" dropdown menu is expanded, displaying a list of available file types. The list is scrolled down to show file types including "WordPerfect 6.0/6.1 (*.wpd;*.wpt)", "RTF Help File (*.rtf)", and "WordPerfect 5.1/5.2 (*.doc)".

The screenshot shows the Corel WordPerfect 7 window with the "Save As" dialog box open. The dialog box is titled "Corel Office - Save As - MyFiles".  The "Save as type:" dropdown menu is expanded and displays a list of available file types. The last item on the list, "WordPerfect 6.0/6.1 [*wpd; *.wp]", is highlighted.

The screenshot shows the Corel WordPerfect 7 window with the "Save As" dialog box open. The dialog box is titled "Corel Office -- Save As - MyFiles".  The "Save as type:" drop-down menu is expanded and displays a list of file types. The list is scrolled down to show file types including "MS Word for Windows 6.0/7.0 (*.doc)" and others.

The screenshot shows the Corel WordPerfect 7 window with the "Save As" dialog box open. The dialog box is titled "Corel Office - Save As - MyFiles".  The "Save as type" dropdown menu is expanded, displaying a list of available file types. 

New UI Elements:
- The "Save As" dialog box is now visible. 
- Within the "Save As" dialog box:
    -  A "Browse" button is present to the right of the "Save in:" field.
    -  A "Save in:" field displays "MyFiles".
    -  A file directory tree is visible, displaying "My Computer", "MyFiles", and "Backup".
    -  A "File name:" field with the default name "*.wpd".
    -  A "Password protect" checkbox.
    -  "Save" and "Close" buttons. 
    -  A status bar at the bottom shows "1 object(s)" and "0 bytes (Disk free space: 1,993GB). 
- The "Save as type" dropdown menu is expanded, showing a list of file types including "WordPerfect 6.0/6.1", various ASCII formats, "EDGAR", "Excel", "HTML", and "Lotus 123".

The screenshot shows a maximized Corel WordPerfect 7 window with the "Save As" dialog box overlayed on top. The dialog box is titled "Corel Office -- Save As - MyFiles."  The "Save in:" field shows "MyFiles" is currently selected. The "File name:" field displays "*.wpd".  The drop-down menu for "As type:" is expanded, displaying a list of available file types. The list is scrolled down to show options including "Lotus 123" and "MS Word for Windows." 

New UI Elements:
- The "Save As" dialog box is now visible. This dialog box allows users to choose a file name, location, and type for saving their document.
- Within the "Save As" dialog box:
    - A "Save in:" field allows users to navigate to the desired save location.
    - A "File name:" field allows users to type a name for the file.
    - An "As type:" drop-down menu allows users to select the file type.
    - A "Password protect" checkbox allows users to add a password to the file.
    - "Save" and "Close" buttons are present. 

Missing UI Elements: None 

Content Changes: None
